channel.title: The Sydney Morning Herald News Headlines
channel.description: The top News headlines from The Sydney Morning Herald. For all the news, visit http://www.smh.com.au.

item.title: Peter, we hardly knew you
item.description: Greg Baum: It is possible to say where he came from, but not where he belonged.

item.title: Roebuck plunges to death from hotel window after police questioning
item.description: PETER ROEBUCK, regarded by many as the finest cricket writer of his generation, fell to his death from a hotel window in Cape Town on Saturday night after being questioned by police about an alleged sexual assault.

item.title: Gillard fights her way back
item.description: Julia Gillard's standing has rebounded strongly while the Coalition continues to hold a commanding lead.

item.title: A rich Harvest for some
item.description: Despite drawing almost 10,000 visitors, yesterday's Harvest Festival may have been a one-off.

item.title: Debt and broken promises
item.description: After being in thrall to Silvio Berlusconi for 17 years, Italy faces life without him, write Rachel Donadio and Elisabetta Povoledo.

item.title: Forget the Gold Coast
item.description: As their classmates flock to the coast for schoolies, a group of school leavers have a different mission in mind.

item.title: Dentists start Botox turf war
item.description: Dentists are giving patients Botox injections and lip enhancements for cosmetic reasons in spite of regulations.

item.title: The point of no return
item.description: At gigs across the country, the encore is being dramatically snubbed.

item.title: Florence has always got more love
item.description: BRITISH superstar Florence Welch is emphatic when it comes to encores. ''I don't think you should do two. One is OK, but two, no way.''
